userDefinedAttribute.comment: This value is used as number of the assigned route when the vehicle is not on a route and passes a static (or partial, partial PT or managed lanes) vehicle routing decision which has the user-defined attribute "UseVehNextRoute" set to true. If the attribute value is zero or negative or empty, the routing decision assigns a random route as normal. If there is no route with that number, no route is assigned.

If the vehicle has a positive value in the user-defined attribute "NextRouteNo", that value is assigned as route number (if that route exists else no route at all). If that attribute value is zero or negative or empty, the routing decision assigns a random route as normal.
